    • openDelay

      public static void openDelay​(int task, int delay)
      Queues a task with a delay, in seconds.
      Parameters:
      task - A number correlating with the event that will fire. 1 opens multiplayer, 2 pings the target, 3 connects to the target. Other values will do nothing.
      delay - The time in seconds until it's called.

    • getServerSelectionList

      public static net.minecraft.client.gui.screen.ServerSelectionList getServerSelectionList​(net.minecraft.client.gui.screen.MultiplayerScreen screen)
      Gets the ServerSelectionList from a MultiplayerScreen.
      Parameters:
      screen - Pass in the MultiplayerScreen that you want to get the ServerSelectionList of.
      Returns:
      Returns the ServerSelectionList, but much more easily accessible. Run .children() and iterate through that to get the individual servers.

    • getServerEntry

      public static net.minecraft.client.gui.screen.ServerSelectionList.NormalEntry getServerEntry​(net.minecraft.client.gui.screen.MultiplayerScreen screen, java.lang.String ip)
      Gets the ServerSelectionList.NormalEntry of a targeted IP.
      Parameters:
      screen - The MultiplayerScreen to check the ServerSelectionList of. DO NOT PASS IN ANY OTHER SCREEN.
      ip - The IP of the requested NormalEntry.
      Returns:
      The NormalEntry of the requested server, null if not found
